01:05:04.738 --> 01:05:07.407
<i>and I had a lot of learning</i>
<i>on the job.</i>

1578
01:05:07.449 --> 01:05:10.326
but I was around the best guys
in the business for that.

1579
01:05:10.368 --> 01:05:12.203
- No fear. man.
Let's go.

1580
01:05:12.245 --> 01:05:14.039
<i>- I would stand</i>
<i>in the backstage</i>

1581
01:05:14.080 --> 01:05:15.623
with Richard Fliehr.

1582
01:05:15.665 --> 01:05:17.417
but when the curtain opened up.
and we walked through.

1583
01:05:17.459 --> 01:05:19.044
I was with Ric Flair.

1584
01:05:19.085 --> 01:05:20.837
<i>and he could feel it.</i>

1585
01:05:20.879 --> 01:05:24.299
<i>He just couldn't carry it</i>
<i>all the time then.</i>

1586
01:05:24.341 --> 01:05:26.009
<i>But it was definitely--</i>
<i>as time went on.</i>

1587
01:05:26.051 --> 01:05:29.471
<i>he was definitely becoming</i>
<i>the Nature Boy again.</i>

1588
01:05:29.512 --> 01:05:31.723
<i>- I'm 55 years old.</i>
<i>and I'm in Evolution.</i>

1589
01:05:31.765 --> 01:05:33.808
and I'm walking down the aisle.

1590
01:05:33.850 --> 01:05:36.353
It was almost like a rib
with Hunter. Dave. and Randy--

1591
01:05:36.394 --> 01:05:38.188
you know. immaculate.

1592
01:05:38.229 --> 01:05:39.814
<i>and I'm physically.</i>

1593
01:05:39.856 --> 01:05:41.566
<i>I mean.</i>
<i>"Please. this is a joke."</i>

1594
01:05:41.608 --> 01:05:44.027
<i>I just wore my robe</i>
<i>as much as possible.</i>

1595
01:05:44.069 --> 01:05:46.654
<i>I never got it back totally.</i>

1596
01:05:46.696 --> 01:05:49.157
<i>It gave me life again.</i>

1597
01:05:49.199 --> 01:05:50.116
<i>It gave me life.</i>

1598
01:05:50.158 --> 01:05:51.576
and I was ready.

1599
01:05:51.618 --> 01:05:54.037
<i>- Flair's done it!</i>
<i>Flair's done it!</i>

1600
01:05:54.079 --> 01:05:57.582
<i>The Nature Boy is</i>
<i>the Intercontinental Champion!</i>

1601
01:05:57.624 --> 01:05:59.084
<i>- Where are we going?</i>

1602
01:05:59.125 --> 01:06:00.377
Woo!
It's LA. Vince.

1603
01:06:00.418 --> 01:06:01.544
We're going down to the strip.

1604
01:06:01.586 --> 01:06:02.837
<i>It's a party!</i>
<i>Woo!</i>

1605
01:06:02.879 --> 01:06:05.507
<i>With the champ!</i>
<i>[laughter]</i>

1606
01:06:06.424 --> 01:06:08.718
<i>- It was easy to assume</i>
<i>that at that time.</i>

1607
01:06:08.760 --> 01:06:11.846
there just couldn't be that
much gas left in the tank.

1608
01:06:11.888 --> 01:06:14.641
<i>and yet. man.</i>

1609
01:06:14.683 --> 01:06:18.812
<i>it turned into a special</i>
<i>next six. seven years</i>

1610
01:06:18.853 --> 01:06:20.522
<i>with so many</i>
<i>memorable moments.</i>

1611
01:06:20.563 --> 01:06:24.901
- And I love being
the Nature Boy!

1612
01:06:24.943 --> 01:06:28.571
<i>* *</i>

1613
01:06:28.613 --> 01:06:31.282
- I don't remember
the actual circumstances.

1614
01:06:31.324 --> 01:06:32.867
but. you know.
it was getting to a point

1615
01:06:32.909 --> 01:06:36.162
where. you know. Evolution
had kind of run its course.

1616
01:06:36.204 --> 01:06:38.123
<i>and he was still kind of doing</i>
<i>the things he was doing.</i>

1617
01:06:38.164 --> 01:06:40.208
<i>but I think he was getting</i>
<i>to a point where people were</i>

1618
01:06:40.250 --> 01:06:42.335
<i>starting to worry</i>
<i>about him in the ring.</i>

1619
01:06:42.377 --> 01:06:44.087
- Ah. shit!

1620
01:06:44.129 --> 01:06:45.338
<i>- I'm not sure he was fully.</i>

1621
01:06:45.380 --> 01:06:46.798
<i>in his mind. ready to retire.</i>

1622
01:06:46.840 --> 01:06:49.551
<i>I think Vince sort of broached</i>

1623
01:06:49.592 --> 01:06:51.344
<i>the subject with him.</i>

1624
01:06:51.386 --> 01:06:52.595
Vince was like.
"Look. there's a reason

1625
01:06:52.637 --> 01:06:54.180
"they put a jockey
on a racehorse.

1626
01:06:54.222 --> 01:06:55.348
"Somebody's gotta
pull the reins.

1627
01:06:55.390 --> 01:06:56.725
or they will run
until they die."

1628
01:06:56.766 --> 01:06:58.518
<i>So the decision was made.</i>

1629
01:06:58.560 --> 01:06:59.728
<i>Like. we'll put you</i>
<i>in the Hall of Fame.</i>

1630
01:06:59.769 --> 01:07:01.396
<i>and then do your last match.</i>

1631
01:07:01.438 --> 01:07:04.983
<i>but that was tough for Ric.</i>

1632
01:07:05.025 --> 01:07:08.111
<i>Everything about Ric</i>
<i>is the Nature Boy Ric Flair.</i>

1633
01:07:08.153 --> 01:07:11.031
<i>* *</i>

1634
01:07:11.072 --> 01:07:14.325
- It's at a moment like this

1635
01:07:14.367 --> 01:07:15.869
when guys like me...

1636
01:07:17.787 --> 01:07:20.749
Say to themselves
for all we've done wrong.

1637
01:07:20.790 --> 01:07:22.208
we must've done
something right.

1638
01:07:22.250 --> 01:07:23.501
[chuckles]

1639
01:07:23.543 --> 01:07:27.464
<i>So I can't tell you how much</i>

1640
01:07:27.505 --> 01:07:29.257
<i>all this means to me.</i>

1641
01:07:29.299 --> 01:07:31.092
<i>* *</i>

1642
01:07:31.134 --> 01:07:33.845
<i>I just wanted everybody</i>
<i>to know along the way.</i>

1643
01:07:33.887 --> 01:07:35.805
people in my life--
and I've had a long life.

1644
01:07:35.847 --> 01:07:37.265
a lot of people
say "thank you."

1645
01:07:37.307 --> 01:07:39.142
<i>* *</i>

1646
01:07:39.184 --> 01:07:41.144
<i>Shawn Michaels.</i>

1647
01:07:41.186 --> 01:07:46.024
<i>I want to wrestle you</i>
<i>at WrestleMania.</i>

1648
01:07:46.066 --> 01:07:48.902
<i>- I think anybody that commits</i>
<i>their life to something.</i>

1649
01:07:48.943 --> 01:07:51.321
um. no matter
what line of work it is.

1650
01:07:51.363 --> 01:07:53.782
but certainly. I think.

1651
01:07:53.823 --> 01:07:57.410
<i>in the athletic field.</i>
<i>it's a big and major decision.</i>

1652
01:07:57.452 --> 01:08:00.330
I honestly wanted
to honor all of that

1653
01:08:00.372 --> 01:08:01.498
<i>in that last match.</i>

1654
01:08:01.539 --> 01:08:03.208
- It would be my honor

1655
01:08:03.249 --> 01:08:05.502
to wrestle you at WrestleMania.

1656
01:08:08.421 --> 01:08:10.173
<i>- Woo!</i>

1657
01:08:10.215 --> 01:08:12.634
<i>* *</i>

1658
01:08:17.972 --> 01:08:19.391
- Programs!

1659
01:08:19.432 --> 01:08:21.518
[scanner beeping]

1660
01:08:21.559 --> 01:08:23.395
- Woo!

1661
01:08:23.436 --> 01:08:25.438
<i>- My life is one incredible</i>
<i>happening after another.</i>

1662
01:08:25.480 --> 01:08:27.816
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

1663
01:08:27.857 --> 01:08:29.818
You know. it's like I said--
for all I've done wrong.

1664
01:08:29.859 --> 01:08:34.197
I must've done something right
somewhere to get all this.

1665
01:08:34.239 --> 01:08:37.117
<i>It's hard</i>
<i>to say goodbye and leave</i>

1666
01:08:37.158 --> 01:08:40.829
<i>something</i>
<i>you've done for so long.</i>

1667
01:08:40.870 --> 01:08:43.206
<i>- The decision for Ric</i>
<i>to retire</i>

1668
01:08:43.248 --> 01:08:45.834
<i>may have been more Vince's</i>
<i>than it was Ric's.</i>

1669
01:08:45.875 --> 01:08:47.752
But also. at the same time.

1670
01:08:47.794 --> 01:08:51.798
I don't remember Ric fighting
it too vigorously either.

1671
01:08:51.840 --> 01:08:53.133
<i>Vince looked at it as.</i>

1672
01:08:53.174 --> 01:08:54.551
<i>"You've had</i>
<i>a hell of a career.</i>

1673
01:08:54.592 --> 01:08:56.845
<i>"but you don't need to be</i>
<i>taking bumps anymore.</i>

1674
01:08:56.886 --> 01:08:58.638
<i>"You don't need to be</i>
<i>in the ring anymore.</i>

1675
01:08:58.680 --> 01:09:00.682
"and let's give you
the send-off

1676
01:09:00.724 --> 01:09:04.936
that's worthy of your career."

1677
01:09:04.978 --> 01:09:09.315
<i>- 2008. WrestleMania XXIV.</i>

1678
01:09:09.357 --> 01:09:12.027
<i>After 36 years of wrestling.</i>

1679
01:09:12.068 --> 01:09:16.781
<i>the WWE ending for Ric Flair</i>
<i>was upon him:</i>

1680
01:09:16.823 --> 01:09:18.992
<i>retirement.</i>

1681
01:09:19.034 --> 01:09:22.537
<i>and his family was ringside</i>
<i>to see it all.</i>

1682
01:09:28.877 --> 01:09:32.005
<i>- He is the best</i>
<i>at what he does.</i>

1683
01:09:32.047 --> 01:09:35.258
and the word "proud"
doesn't even describe.

1684
01:09:35.300 --> 01:09:36.926
you know. I guess.

1685
01:09:36.968 --> 01:09:38.553
how any of us feel
in the family

1686
01:09:38.595 --> 01:09:40.930
<i>about what he's done.</i>

1687
01:09:40.972 --> 01:09:42.432
- He'll go down in history

1688
01:09:42.474 --> 01:09:44.476
as the greatest wrestler
of all time.

1689
01:09:44.517 --> 01:09:47.854
<i>- It's a great feeling to know</i>
<i>that you have someone</i>

1690
01:09:47.896 --> 01:09:49.147
that's in your family
that's appreciated

1691
01:09:49.189 --> 01:09:50.607
by more than just you.

1692
01:09:50.648 --> 01:09:52.484
I mean. he's appreciated
by so many people.

1693
01:09:52.525 --> 01:09:55.070
all: Woo!

1694
01:09:55.111 --> 01:09:56.988
- Ric Flair. baby!
both: Woo!

1695
01:09:57.030 --> 01:09:59.616
<i>- Woo!</i>

1696
01:09:59.657 --> 01:10:01.701
- He'll be happy.
but at the same time.

1697
01:10:01.743 --> 01:10:04.204
you know. sad. remorseful

1698
01:10:04.245 --> 01:10:06.915
that. you know.
what he's done his whole life.

1699
01:10:06.956 --> 01:10:08.500
<i>it's coming to an end.</i>

1700
01:10:08.541 --> 01:10:12.212
<i>* *</i>

1701
01:10:12.253 --> 01:10:14.422
<i>- I'm in Orlando. getting</i>
<i>ready to wrestle Shawn.</i>

1702
01:10:14.464 --> 01:10:15.965
<i>and I was just nervous</i>

1703
01:10:16.007 --> 01:10:18.802
and insecure
as I've ever been in my life.

1704
01:10:18.843 --> 01:10:23.056
<i>* *</i>

1705
01:10:23.098 --> 01:10:26.768
<i>- It was something</i>
<i>that I really took seriously:</i>

1706
01:10:26.810 --> 01:10:30.522
his image and his legacy.
all of those things.

1707
01:10:30.563 --> 01:10:32.232
<i>I understood and appreciated</i>

1708
01:10:32.273 --> 01:10:33.983
<i>how important those things</i>
<i>were to him.</i>

1709
01:10:34.025 --> 01:10:37.445
<i>and I honestly wanted</i>
<i>to honor all of that</i>

1710
01:10:37.487 --> 01:10:38.571
<i>in that last match.</i>

1711
01:10:38.613 --> 01:10:40.365
<i>* *</i>

1712
01:10:40.407 --> 01:10:42.951
<i>- He said. "Just shut up</i>
<i>and listen to me tonight.</i>

1713
01:10:42.992 --> 01:10:44.494
<i>Don't say a word."</i>

1714
01:10:44.536 --> 01:10:46.579
<i>I went. "Well. okay."</i>

1715
01:10:46.621 --> 01:10:49.249
No wrestler's
ever said that to me.

1716
01:10:49.290 --> 01:10:51.292
<i>And we--we're standing there.</i>
<i>and he said. "Let's do this."</i>

1717
01:10:51.334 --> 01:10:53.712
all: Woo!

1718
01:10:53.753 --> 01:10:55.296
<i>- Went out there</i>
<i>and made music.</i>

1719
01:10:55.338 --> 01:10:57.090
<i>Woo!</i>

1720
01:10:57.132 --> 01:11:00.176
["Also sprach Zarathustra"
by Richard Strauss]

1721
01:11:00.218 --> 01:11:07.142
<i>* *</i>

1722
01:11:12.355 --> 01:11:14.941
<i>People were going crazy.</i>

1723
01:11:14.983 --> 01:11:16.776
I started crying
on the way down.

1724
01:11:16.818 --> 01:11:19.779
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

1725
01:11:19.821 --> 01:11:26.953
<i>* *</i>

1726
01:11:29.164 --> 01:11:31.875
<i>- I really don't think</i>
<i>I realized</i>

1727
01:11:31.916 --> 01:11:35.837
how important my dad was
to the wrestling world

1728
01:11:35.879 --> 01:11:38.465
until he retired.

1729
01:11:38.506 --> 01:11:40.717
<i>To see 70.000 people crying</i>

1730
01:11:40.759 --> 01:11:43.720
<i>over this man was incredible.</i>

1731
01:11:43.762 --> 01:11:49.559
<i>* *</i>

1732
01:11:49.601 --> 01:11:50.977
- Woo!

1733
01:11:51.019 --> 01:11:52.604
<i>- Everybody's eyes watered up.</i>

1734
01:11:52.645 --> 01:11:55.648
<i>It is still</i>
<i>one of those hallmark moments</i>

1735
01:11:55.690 --> 01:11:58.068
that everybody who watches it

1736
01:11:58.109 --> 01:12:00.028
<i>went back to where I went to.</i>

1737
01:12:00.070 --> 01:12:03.490
<i>which is being that</i>
<i>15-year-old wrestling fan.</i>

1738
01:12:03.531 --> 01:12:08.787
<i>* *</i>

1739
01:12:08.828 --> 01:12:10.997
- Woo!

1740
01:12:11.039 --> 01:12:13.041
<i>- There it is: vintage Flair.</i>

1741
01:12:13.083 --> 01:12:15.001
[bell dings]
<i>Vintage Nature Boy!</i>

1742
01:12:15.043 --> 01:12:17.337
<i>Oh. look out!</i>
<i>[laughs]</i>

1743
01:12:17.379 --> 01:12:20.799
<i>Flair wanted to be in the ring</i>
<i>with the best.</i>

1744
01:12:20.840 --> 01:12:23.426
<i>- And now Flair</i>
<i>climbing to the top!</i>

1745
01:12:23.468 --> 01:12:24.386
<i>- Look at this!</i>

1746
01:12:25.637 --> 01:12:28.973
- To me. it was mostly
trying to stay focused

1747
01:12:29.015 --> 01:12:32.519
<i>and relatively unemotional.</i>

1748
01:12:32.560 --> 01:12:33.812
<i>- Uh-oh.</i>
<i>- Oh!</i>

1749
01:12:34.729 --> 01:12:36.773
<i>- I know how much</i>
<i>that match meant to Shawn.</i>

1750
01:12:36.815 --> 01:12:38.274
<i>'cause he felt the same way.</i>

1751
01:12:38.316 --> 01:12:40.902
<i>growing up.</i>
<i>about Ric that I did.</i>

1752
01:12:40.944 --> 01:12:42.195
<i>I usually</i>
<i>don't have the chance</i>

1753
01:12:42.237 --> 01:12:44.030
to watch other matches
at WrestleMania.

1754
01:12:44.072 --> 01:12:45.573
I watched every second
of that match.

1755
01:12:45.615 --> 01:12:47.033
<i>* *</i>

1756
01:12:47.075 --> 01:12:49.035
<i>- Michaels said</i>
<i>that he was gonna</i>

1757
01:12:49.077 --> 01:12:50.578
<i>take Flair out behind the barn</i>

1758
01:12:50.620 --> 01:12:51.955
<i>and put him out of his misery.</i>

1759
01:12:51.996 --> 01:12:53.665
<i>but in the heart</i>
<i>of Shawn Michaels.</i>

1760
01:12:53.707 --> 01:12:54.874
<i>can he do it?</i>

1761
01:12:54.916 --> 01:12:58.003
<i>* *</i>

1762
01:12:58.044 --> 01:13:01.006
- What does Shawn say to you

1763
01:13:01.047 --> 01:13:03.591
<i>before the match concludes?</i>

1764
01:13:03.633 --> 01:13:09.597
<i>* *</i>

1765
01:13:09.639 --> 01:13:10.932
<i>- "I'm sorry."</i>

1766
01:13:12.392 --> 01:13:13.435
<i>"I love you."</i>

1767
01:13:13.476 --> 01:13:19.441
<i>* *</i>

1768
01:13:29.034 --> 01:13:30.118
<i>[heartbeat thumps]</i>

1769
01:13:32.454 --> 01:13:33.371
<i>[heartbeat thumps]</i>

1770
01:13:37.208 --> 01:13:38.585
<i>[boom]</i>

1771
01:13:38.626 --> 01:13:39.586
[bell dings]

1772
01:13:39.627 --> 01:13:42.547
<i>[crowd cheering]</i>

1773
01:13:49.637 --> 01:13:54.267
<i>* *</i>

1774
01:13:54.309 --> 01:13:56.436
<i>- It is real. raw emotion.</i>

1775
01:13:56.478 --> 01:13:58.396
and in a line of work

1776
01:13:58.438 --> 01:14:01.441
where we're all
a bunch of grown freaking men

1777
01:14:01.483 --> 01:14:06.654
that are paid. sometimes.
to put up walls and act tough.

1778
01:14:06.696 --> 01:14:09.491
<i>that was just me.</i>
<i>Shawn Hickenbottom.</i>

1779
01:14:09.532 --> 01:14:11.493
<i>telling Richard Fliehr.</i>

1780
01:14:11.534 --> 01:14:12.786
"I think the world of you."

1781
01:14:12.827 --> 01:14:16.164
<i>* *</i>

1782
01:14:16.206 --> 01:14:19.959
[cheers and applause]

1783
01:14:20.001 --> 01:14:21.920
<i>- Man. that reception...</i>

1784
01:14:21.961 --> 01:14:24.047
<i>I couldn't believe</i>
<i>the response.</i>

1785
01:14:24.089 --> 01:14:25.632
<i>* *</i>

1786
01:14:25.674 --> 01:14:27.634
I looked to my right.
and there's my family.

1787
01:14:27.676 --> 01:14:34.557
<i>* *</i>

1788
01:14:37.352 --> 01:14:40.355
<i>- It was the first time</i>
<i>that my siblings</i>

1789
01:14:40.397 --> 01:14:42.273
<i>had all been together</i>
<i>in a long time.</i>

1790
01:14:42.315 --> 01:14:44.818
<i>and seeing my dad wrestle--</i>

1791
01:14:44.859 --> 01:14:47.153
just what
an emotional roller coaster.

1792
01:14:47.195 --> 01:14:49.781
and just seeing my little
brother just. like. bawling

1793
01:14:49.823 --> 01:14:51.991
<i>and my dad kissing him. and...</i>

1794
01:14:52.033 --> 01:14:54.577
<i>Like. I don't think</i>
<i>many wrestlers</i>

1795
01:14:54.619 --> 01:14:58.248
<i>get to have</i>
<i>a farewell like that.</i>

1796
01:14:58.289 --> 01:14:59.916
<i>- My heart just hurt for him.</i>

